{"key":"post-12914529","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12914529</id>\n<content>Personally, I disagree strongly with attempts to automate a terrarium, especially by new growers just learning the ropes.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;When you mist a few times daily, it gives a chance to really inspect the substrate for any sign of mold.&amp;nbsp; If you automate it, you might go too long without looking and find the darned thing covered with mold, puking trillions of trichoderma spores into your growing area.&amp;nbsp; Misting by hand also lets you read each substrate and determine exactly how much to mist.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As already said, the MMGG is outdated, but was crappy at best ten years ago.&amp;nbsp; Fruiting parameters for mushrooms haven't changed in thousands of years. . .we just know a lot more about them now.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>12914267</prev>\n<first>12913571</first>\n<last>12914529</last>\n<when>1279460542</when>\n<utime>07/18/10 04:42 PM</utime>\n</post>"}